Last year, during the 2020-2021 NCAA Men's Basketball season, the head coach of the Michigan Wolverines basketball team was Juwan Howard. Howard, a former NBA player and member of the Fab Five, was in his second season as head coach of the Wolverines, having taken over the role in 2019. Under Howard's leadership, the Wolverines had a successful season in 2020-2021, finishing with a record of 23-5 and making it to the Elite Eight of the NCAA Tournament.